    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/54.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cables June 22 and 23 received. Government of Liberia have complied with their
                    suggestions. Falkner’s commissions will meet him in Hamburg. Program as outlined
                    by our Government is approved. They want our Government to define the duties of
                    the financial adviser for legislative action, as this was the cause of trouble
                    before. A memorandum to Falkner suggests the following:</p>
                <p>First, loan to be not more than two millions, to run fifty years at not more than
                    5 per cent; second, amortization for the first twenty-five <pb facs="0426"
                        n="344" xml:id="pg_344"/> years not more than 1 per cent or less; third,
                    provisions be made for a working bank credit of one hundred thousand
                    annually.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lyon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
